@manobassa: there's a bit of a loophole, especially concerning tv shows. People have been recording shows and sharing them since the ability to do so became available, most notably with the VCR. The only difference is that it is now easier and faster to do so. TV shows are already broadcast for free (except on cable) with no copyright notice. Always have been. The MPAA are just whining because they didn't think things through far enough. So long as you are not making money from copyrighted material, there really is no problem.
